Empowerment. Engagement. Respect.             The Asian American Resource and Cultural Center supports the needs of Asian Americans at UIC and offers social, cultural, and educational programs to those interested in expanding their knowledge about Asian Americans.  COVID-19 Response:  Effective March 16 and until further notice, AARCC staff will be working remotely and will hold the reduced business hours of 10:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m. due to staffing limitations and to practice healthy social-distancing.   Please email AARCC@uic.edu or call 312-413-9569 and someone will respond during business hours.   All upcoming AARCC Lunchbox programs and community programs have been cancelled until further notice.  Please visit this page and our Facebook Page for any updates.   For the latest news and information about COVID-19 to the campus community, visit https://today.uic.edu/coronavirus .
